name: Rendezvous Hair Salon
comment: The whole salon is EXTREMELY trans and gender-non-conforming friendly!

name: REfuse cafe
directions: This is on the Main Street of Chester le st, a 5 minute walk from multiple car parks and bus stops.
comment: A fab cafe which offers a ‘pay as you feel’ service for food made from donations which would usually be going to waste.

name: Café St Henri
street: 849 Rue Saint-Joseph E, Québec, QC G1K 3C8
directions: Au fond en bas des marches
comment: Il faut idéalement être client mais ils sont assez compréhensifs

name: 877 Rue de la Marée-Haute, Québec, QC G1K 8T7, Canada
directions: Premier couloir à gauche en entrant près du Chez Victor.
comment: C'est dans le building principal(Telus) mais facilité si vs êtes clients du restaurant chez Victor. Ils ont une affiche indiquant que tous sont acceptés entre autre.

name: Kirjasto / Main Library
directions: The second floor, single room, accessible restroom.
comment: May or may not require a key. Quiet and unassuming place.

name: The Whig
directions: Go down the stairs into the bar, turn left around the kitchen, hallways turns left again and it’s at the end.
comment: Bar is run by good people and shouldn’t give you trouble unless you seem/are underage.

name: Murchiston House
directions: Go up ramp to enter the building and turn left. Go about 20m straight ahead and bathroom is on the right.
comment:
Make note of hours/times of year when a valid University of Edinburgh ID card must be shown for access to the building. Usually from 9-5 during term times (September to April) they are open to general public but check the website here: https://www.ed.ac.uk/information-services/library-museum-gallery/using-library/library-opening/murray-library-opening

Bathrooms are gender neutral with near floor to ceiling doors (small gap at the bottom).

name: Kurumi clinic
directions: It is the innermost part of the 1st floor.
comment: For visiting patients.

name: Villa Ridge Garden Centre/Patio Rose Cafe
directions: Walk through the cafe and there are 2 non-gendered stalls on the left.
comment: Very chill atmosphere. No need to buy anything!

name: Willa Jean
comment: Still separate bathrooms, but labeled as she/her/them and he/him/them.

name: 2-chōme-23-5 Ōhara, Setagaya City, Tokyo 156-0041, Japan
directions: It is the innermost part of the 1st floor.
comment: For visiting patients.

name: Cuppa Austin
directions: In the back

name: CHC
directions: Second floor across from the pharmacy
comment: There are single room “male” and “female” restrooms. Use whichever one feels right to you, it’s a safe building.

name: Kohl's
comment: It is a family restroom that can be used by an gender and no one will bat an eye if you go in there

name: PHIIRST (Philadelphia Institute for Individual, Relational and Sex Therapy)
Banheiro Unissex no Grand Plaza Shopping
directions: Ao lado da praça de alimentação.
comment: Possui mais de 50 cabines.

name: Banheiro Unissex no Grand Plaza Shopping
directions: Ao lado da praça de alimentação.
comment: Possui mais de 50 cabines.

name: Target
directions: Just inside the main entrance of Target to the right.
comment: Target has a national policy of allowing everyone to use the restroom for the gender they identify as.

name: Coffee Culture
directions: Washrooms at the back
comment: Trans friendly and supportive of whatever bathrooms you identify as needing

name: Chandler MMA
comment: This business is inclusive and welcoming of all individuals

name: All Bodies Massage
directions: Suite 101
comment: Office is open by appointment only so may or may not be open if just passing through but it is a safe space.

name: Fred Meyers
directions: As you head down to the gender bathrooms you pass it on the left first, by drinking fountain

name: Bexley Coffee Shop
comment: You have to be a paying customer, but there are plenty of yummy selections.

name: Gnome Games Green Bay West
directions: Go to the right when you walk in.  All the way to the back on the left near the exit in the play side of the store.
comment: Staff are friendly and will ask what you are shopping for.  Being a paid customer is not required.

name: Life Sciences Building
directions: Single "all gender" bathroom on basement level of building. Take elevator to easily get to basement level.

name: The Cosmos
directions: The restrooms near the patio.
comment: The restrooms near the patio are labeled all-gender and are single stall restrooms.

name: Winner's Home Sense
directions: First door on the right, single stall, puch button to lock, will light up red when locked.

name: Trading Post 49
directions: At the back of the store to the right
comment: Ask the clerk to use the restroom, they will let you in. The bathroom is a single room that can be used by any sex/gender.

name: Cornerstone Services
directions: Front office past the door.

name: Starbucks
directions: at the corner of Queens Boulevard and 67th Road. Bathroom is labeled "all gender" and located in the back of the shop
comment: atmosphere is friendly

name: Starbucks
directions: back of the store

name: Starbucks
directions: back of the store

name: Scott Building - KDOR
comment: Employees only - 100% gender-safe no matter what gender you id with

name: Starbucks
directions: From the parking lot entrance, to the left immediately upon entering.
comment: Anyone can use the restroom; don't need to be a paying customer.

name: Beetle House LA
directions: If on the bar side, go straight to the back. There are two gendered bathrooms (which are both safe spaces) as well as an all-gender bathroom. If on the reservations only side, go to the back, make a right at the dressing rooms, and it’ll be on your left
comment: This is a restaurant that does shows, so you will most likely need to have a reservation

name: Bodacious Bookstore & Cafe
directions: At the back by the bookstore cash register
comment: At least browse, but make a purchase if you can!

name: Mt. San Jacinto College - Temecula Valley Campus
directions: Every bathroom in all five floors are unisex

name: The French Market Creperie
directions: Bathrooms are down the hall on the right, after the front counter where you place your order.
comment: Bathrooms are an open safe bathroom space

name: People Under the Staircase
comment: All bathrooms in the building are gender neutral; only the first floor bathroom is accessible

name: Starbucks
directions: When you come in to the store, it’s on the right after the seating area.

name: Fergusons Downtown
directions: Several bathrooms around the shopping mall.
comment: Open to the public!

name: Target Southridge
directions: Immediately to the left inside the main doors

name: Miller/Main Administration Building
directions: Single stall, marked gender neutral, only bathroom on the second floor (so anyone on the second floor can give you directions). Bathroom is located between the elevator and the main conference room.
comment: Very clean, frequently empty. Make sure to lock the door!

name: McHenry Library
directions: Located on the ground floor to the right of the vending machines. Use the elevators or the south stairs on the entry level of the library.
comment: Library hours subject to change. Open to students, staff, and public. Only all-gender restroom at McHenry.

name: Gryphon Building
comment: You must have a code to use the restrooms, if you go to the restaurant on the first floor they will give you the code

name: Slapfish
comment: Private, clean, large, accessible.

name: Preble Rest Area
directions: Instead of turning left or right for gendered restrooms, in the center is a single stall, accessible, unisex rest room.
comment: Free for any visitor. I forgot to check for changing table, so there might be one, but I didn't want to check "yes" just in case.

name: Sub - Schwules Kommunikations- und Kulturzentrum München e.V.
comment: Queer friendly café

name: Dollar Tree
directions: End of aisle 2, through the white door

name: Blue Bar Quilts
directions: Towards the back of the shop on the left.

name: Community Beyond Violence
directions: Take the ramp to the second floor, there are bathrooms in the hallway, and services if needed at the front office at the end on the right. This door is only unlocked during their business hours. (M-F 9-5)

name: Snooze, an AM Eatery
directions: Straight in through the door and to the back.
comment: We were customers, but it is unlikely that there would be a complaint if one needed to run in and use the facilities. Clean and well stocked, and my best friend had no issues during our visit.

name: Manor Hill Tavern
directions: Second floor, turn left (towards the patio exit), and take the next left down the hallway.
comment: There are 2 single occupancy unisex restrooms

name: Northwest Mutual Community Park
directions: Four family/unisex bathrooms available. All have child and adult changing tables as well. Volunteer said ALL are welcome to the facilities.

name: Meininger Art Supply
directions: Front of the store on the left hand side.
comment: For “paying customers”, just browse for a bit. Store is an LGBTQIA+ safe space.

name: Harrisburg IL District Library
directions: Both restrooms on the main floor are accessible and gender neutral.
comment: restrooms are near the back entrance.

name: Egyptian Health Department
directions: Ask for gender neutral restroom at front door
comment: preferred that restrooms behind the double doors are for clients but staff will allow access to additional restrooms as needed

name: Parkside
comment: They have a pride rainbow on the door

name: Greater Victoria public library - Nellie McClung branch
directions: Go in, turn left, then left again to a small hallway
comment: All are welcome at the library. There are both gendered bathrooms and a single unisex one.

name: Lokum Stonewall
comment: Lokal przyjazny osobom lgbtq+

name: Mountview
directions: As you enter through the main entrance you need to head for the door furthest to the right on the back wall; the gender neutral bathrooms are through there (there's a sign pointing to them).
comment: This is a working drama school and theatre so reception MAY ask if they can assist you or why you are there as you enter the building, but are normally fine to just let you head through to use the bathrooms.

name: Jerry's Valero
directions: Right near cash register, single unisex bathroom, large
comment: Gas station no need to buy anything

name: Happy goat coffee house
directions: At your left after entering the place

name: The Hub
directions: Down the hall behind the coffee counter and first door on the right.
comment: No need to be a customer. This is a safe place for all people to just be. There is a coffee counter that sells coffee drinks and other items. There is also a small gift shop and meeting rooms and a large event room. This space is mainly utilized by individuals in recovery.

name: La Cage - Brasserie Sportive
directions: Seule salle de bain du restaurant, non-genrée et pour tous

name: Roseburg Public Library
directions: Go straight inside and it will be off to you right at the back by two meeting rooms.

name: Tumwater Timberland Library
directions: When you enter the first set of doors, there's a hallway to the left, at the end are the restrooms.
comment: Bathrooms are technicaly gendered, but there is clear signage indicating that users are welcome to choose the bathroom with their preferred gender identity. (There is also a single occupancy stall inside the building, if patrons are still not comfortable with these options). -- From a former employee

name: Tumwater Timberland Library
directions: If you go in the doors and head towards the back corner, there is a single-occupancy unisex bathroom with a changing table near the children's area.
comment: Anyone can use it, it's not just limited to people with children.

name: Olympia Timberland Library
directions: In the back hallway

name: Remedy Cafe
directions: On main floor to the far left when facing the ordering counter. These were ‘male’ and ‘female’ multi-stall rooms. But they now have handwritten signs that say ‘urinal’ or ‘non- urinal’. During covid restrictions, there are also signs that say one person at a time in the whole room. So a bit more safe.
comment: For customers only but it’s an order at the till style place, so easy to go the the restroom first then get something to go. (Or look at menu on wall and change your mind…)

name: West Warwick Public Library
directions: All bathrooms in this building are all gender. Anyone is welcome to come in and use them.
comment: This library is a safe and supportive space for all. It is staffed entirely by Queer folks and allys.

name: Molly Emmons
comment: It is not always open to the public but it is 💯 supportive and affirming of the trans community

name: M&S convenience store in BP petrol station
directions: At the back on the right
comment: No access restrictions

name: Highland County District Library
directions: First door on left and on right in hallway.
comment: Single stall rooms. Both are unisex. Restroom on the right has a changing table.

name: The Buzz Cafe
directions: Through the cafe, up the stairs on the left.
comment: Just ask, they are very friendly.

name: Fox meadows creamery
directions: Behind the little market, next to the ice cream display window.

name: Marmalade
directions: At the back of the shop.
comment: Can use even if you don’t buy anything

name: The Hub
directions: Done the hallways behind the coffee counter to the right.

name: Dish Society
directions: Next to the order counter.
comment: LGBTQ+ friendly, many LGBTQ+ employees. The food is also amazing and allergy friendly if you’re looking for a bite.

name: Costa Coffee
directions: Up the stairs on the right hand side after some tables.
comment: 2 separate bathrooms. Both gender neutral.

name: GEORGE'S SURF 'N TURF
directions: Behind the building, follow the footprints!
comment: I guess you should be a paying customer, but everything is outside, so it works be hard for them to know for sure.
